		<div id="comment_body_64210128"><p>From TFA:</p><p><div class="quote"><p>Hydrogen is hard and expensive to transport, opens new tab and store, with exceedingly low temperatures needed to create liquid hydrogen and high leakage rates for gaseous hydrogen.</p></div><p>They're not thinking it through: just use one oxygen atom as a handy carrying handle for two hydrogen atoms, and hey presto, it becomes really easy to transport.</p></div>
